Let's give a warm welcome to Lisa, we are so excited to have her join our "E" Team!
My name is Lisa Dorow and I'm the new Interventionist/Title I Advisor. I am excited to be part of the MNCS staff and getting to know the students, families, and community. I'm a graduate of Fairmont High School, South Dakota State University, and Bemidji State University. As you can tell, I love LEARNING!! I am relocating back to the St. Peter area with my husband, Jonathan, and our 4 children (Alex, Ian, Joe, & Dru). In our spare time, we love doing arts and crafts, exploring, kayaking, trying new foods, & learning new things. I look forward to supporting MNCS students and families throughout the year.

post_text:
Danielle‚Äôs Trip to the great North Shore!

Hi everyone! My family and I recently spent some time on the North Shore. This is an almost sunset shot in Duluth. We stayed on the point- the other side of the Aerial Lift Bridge. It was neat because you had to be in tune to when ships are entering the harbor so that you don't get stuck on one side and all night long we heard clanging ship noises..it was a maritime experience and adventure. Another part I love is driving up the coast and stopping at small rocky beaches and rock hunting. The lake was so cold it turns your feet numb! I love the color, intensity and vastness of Lake Superior. I've been going there since I was a kid, and when I get that first view of it coming into town my heart goes crazy. It was challenging traveling during a pandemic, but we Minnesotans are lucky that we have some gorgeous outdoors! So get out there!

post_text:
Let‚Äôs give a shout out to Carrie Rice and her new role at MNCS.
Carrie Rice is not new to MNCS. Her husband David taught here for fifteen years and she has worked as a paraprofessional at the elementary and the high school the last several years. Just prior to moving to Henderson three years ago, Carrie left a 20+ career in government relations in the telecommunications industry. She is so looking forward to her new career as an Advisor at the high school helping young people discover a passion for teaching themselves new things!

Carrie and David share their Henderson home with two dogs, two cats and a multitude of plants. She loves to cook and entertain friends and speaks French.

All of the above is true, but since New Countrians love a good round of Two Truths and a Lie, see if you can guess the falsehood:

Carrie has lived with a cat in her life since she was five.
At one point, Carrie had six dogs under her roof
Carrie once had an Appaloosa named Gizmo

post_text:
Let‚Äôs give Nick Ryan a ‚Äúwoot woot‚Äù

I'm excited to be moving back into an advisor role for this coming school year! I'll still be attempting to keep our technology running and managing our assessments as well. My summer has been fun so far. I took my two kids to the BWCA for the first time, the bugs and weather were very forgiving and everyone had a blast! With trail races cancelled it's been hard to stay motivated to run, so this past weekend I ran 40 1 mile laps around my neighborhood as part of a last runner standing event. I wasn't the last runner standing, but it was still fun. It takes a lot of pringles to run 40 miles!

Today is also National System Administrator Appreciation Day! At MNCS If technical issues are at a stall, Nick Ryan is there to answer that call.

post_text:
Please help us welcome Adam Herd to our MNCS Community!

My name is Adam Herd
I am the new 4th/5th grade advisor
I enjoy watching and playing sports, but my favorite is basketball. I also enjoy hiking, playing games like Settlers of Catan and Cribbage, and spending time with my family.
My family consists of my mom (Lisa), dad (James), my brother (Jacob), and his new fiance (Anna).
I was born and raised in Waconia, MN, but attended Grand Canyon University in Phoenix, AZ for my Bachelor's. During the summers of my college years, I lived and worked in Hawaii, Alaska, and Crane Lake, MN. I learned a lot from those opportunities to travel.
I am excited to be back in Minnesota and I am ready to meet all of the wonderful people in this community!

post_text:
Dear MNCS families, your thoughts on Distance Learning are needed! Please share widely and complete the MDE School Fall Planning Survey link below:

http://sgiz.mobi/s3/2020-Parent-Distance-Learning-Feedback-Survey

As the Minnesota Department of Education works closely with the Minnesota Department of Health to plan for the 2020-21 school year, we want to hear from families about their experience with distance learning this spring. We want to know what went well and what schools should do differently if they use distance learning again in the future. This information will be shared with schools through guidance created by MDE. We look forward to hearing from you.

This feedback is extremely valuable to us. This information will allow us to help families as they balance the responsibilities of work and family, while also supporting student learning.

The survey is available in English, Hmong, Somali, and Spanish.

Please share this survey widely with your families and on social media. The survey will close on June 30, 2020.

Thank you!

**Updated** Join us on Saturday, May 30th at 12:45 for a pre-celebration while MNCS Seniors parade their decorated cars escorted down by Henderson Fire Department. Hold up signs, make some noise and show our Seniors how proud we are of them.

Route: Starting at Bender park in Henderson, travel down Main St. to 6th St. take a right (past the park), and another right on to Market St. continue past the Fire Station to MNCS Parking lot where Graduates and their Families will be directed to park.

Graduation Ceremony will be held in the MNCS parking lot at 1:00 pm for MNCS Seniors and their Family only.

MNCS Chopped - S1E1 (and there will be many more)
Students were challenged to prepare a decadent dessert including an onion (yes I said onion) and Spicy Sweet Chili Doritos. To be paired with the main dish that needed to incorporate Strawberry Jello and Goya Ham Seasoning. Other Ingredients they needed to include were: macaroni noodles, pur√©ed pumpkin, Ôøºchocolate pudding, and condensed milk.
The students looked up or created recipes, and were given $25 to purchase supplies, along with access to staples in our kitchen.
What a great experience! The students were so creative and so proud, even if they got CHOPPED!

post_text:
PINOCCHIO is coming to town! We're not lying! Prairie Fire Children's Theatre (PFCT) is coming back to MNCS-Elem to help us with our very own theatre production. It's an all-school "play-in-a-week" that's cast and rehearsed all through the first week of March, ending with TWO BIG PERFORMANCES ON FRIDAY, MARCH 6TH. Please mark your calendars for:

What? "Pinocchio" plays with MNCS-Elem and Prairie Fire Children's Theatre
When? Friday, March 6th at 1:30pm, and also at 6pm
Where? Roadhaus Event Center (dwtn Henderson at 514 Main St)
Who? Play performed by MNCS-Elem students, and all are welcome to attend shows!
Cost to attend? Pay-what-you-want and goodwill donations accepted at the door.

And a word of thanks!... This activity is funded, in part, by the Prairie Lakes Regional Arts Council with an appropriation from the Minnesota State Legislature with money from the state's general fund.

post_text:
The MNCS Archery Team attended the OWL Open in St Paul on Saturday, February 22.
Emmett Ische ended up with two 50's at 10 meters (earning two arrowheads) and a final score of 285. He placed 3rd for 9th grade boys, 6th for high school boys, 7th out of 301 boys and 12th out of 574 total shooters. Congratulations Emmett!

Students who PR'd: Sam Baxa, Emmett Ische, Isaac Kranz, Henry Reinitz and Mae Ringquist

Students who scored in the Top 10 of their grade level:
6th Grade: Brad Petsch - 5th, Sam Baxa - 7th
9th Grade: Emmett Ische - 3rd
12th Grade: Isaac Kranz - 9th

Good job MNCS Archery Team!

Looking for a little extra cash? Speech Coach Jennifer Brunick is looking for Saturday speech judges. It pays $75 and includes lunch.
You must:
*pass a background check
*be a highschool graduate
*have some speech and/or theater experience
*have your own transportation
*meet with Jenn for a brief training
Please email her at jbrunick@newcountryschool.com if interested. Thank you!

post_text: Our fundraiser was so much fun today! We even got a visitor from our past MNCS speech captain/2019 graduate. (In fact several past graduates stopped by to support the team.
